				<a href="http://tastykitchen.com/recipes/drinks/cherry-lime-rickey-iced-tea/">			<img src="http://static.tastykitchen.com/recipes/files/2012/03/IMG_4066-2-270x179.jpg" width="270" alt="" class="yellow-border" itemprop="photo"/>
			</a>
			</div>
			<div class="recent-recipe-info">
				<img src="http://static.tastykitchen.com/recipes/files/avatars/79121/7cf3d4f13ea48e8e272f21a75aeb774b-bpthumb.jpg" alt="Avatar Image" class="avatar user-79121-avatar" width='65' height='65' />				<h2><a href="http://tastykitchen.com/recipes/drinks/cherry-lime-rickey-iced-tea/">Cherry Lime Rickey Iced Tea</a></h2>
				<p class="by">by <a href="http://tastykitchen.com/recipes/members/cuteasacupcake/" title="{Karen} Where Flours Bloom">{Karen} Where Flours Bloom</a> and filed in <a href="http://tastykitchen.com/recipes/category/drinks/" title="View all posts in Drinks" rel="category tag">Drinks</a></p>
				<p>Cherry Lime Rickey Iced Tea recipe made skipping the heat.  Steep a large quantity of tea bags in room-temperature water for a strong-flavored brew without the bitterness. Instead of granulated sugar,  sweeten the tea with simple syrup. Flavor the syrup with lime zest and cherry juice for a unique iced tea.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="recent-recipe-meta">
